---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
const updated = '30 June 2026';
// TODO: keep this accurate to the tools you actually load. If you stick to a cookieless analytics tool
// (Plausible/Fathom), you can run without a consent banner. If you add tools that set non-essential
// cookies, you must add a consent banner and update this page.
---
<Legal
  title="Cookie Policy | CyberCap"
  description="How CyberCap uses cookies and similar technologies."
  heading="Cookie Policy"
  updated={updated}
>
  <p>
    This Cookie Policy explains how <strong>{site.name}</strong> uses cookies and similar technologies on this website.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Our approach</h2>
  <p>
    We keep tracking to a minimum. Our website is designed to work without non-essential cookies. We use a
    privacy-friendly analytics tool that does not use cookies to identify you and does not track you across
    other websites, so we do not display intrusive cookie banners for advertising.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Cookies we use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Strictly necessary</strong> — a small number of technical cookies may be required for the site to function and be served securely. These do not require consent under the GDPR/ePrivacy rules.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics (privacy-friendly)</strong> — aggregated, anonymous usage statistics. [Confirm the tool you use, e.g. Plausible or Fathom, and whether it is cookieless.]</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Third-party content</h2>
  <p>
    If you choose to book a call, our scheduling provider's embedded tool may set its own cookies when you
    interact with it. Please refer to that provider's cookie/privacy policy for details.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Managing cookies</h2>
  <p>
    You can control and delete cookies through your browser settings. Blocking strictly necessary cookies may
    affect how the site works.
  </p>

  <h2>5. More information</h2>
  <p>See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for how we handle personal data, or contact us at <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.</p>

  <p class="mt-10 text-sm text-slate"><em>This document is a template provided to help you launch. Please confirm it matches the tools you load and have it reviewed before relying on it.</em></p>
</Legal>
